articles.description: David Jenkins Jr. had 24 points on 10-of-15 shooting and South Dakota State beat North Dakota State 78-57 in the Summit League Tournament semifinals on Monday night.
articles.headline: South Dakota State beats North Dakota State 78-57

articles.description: Roland Griffin scored a career-high 29 points, Zach Lewis added 20, and Iona beat Fairfield 83-71 on Monday night to capture the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Tournament title for the third straight time and earn the conference's automatic bid to...
articles.headline: Griffin scores 29, Iona beats Fairfield 83-71 for MAAC title

images.caption: After defeating Fairfield in the MAAC championship  Iona clinches a spot in the NCAA tournament.
images.name: Iona punches its ticket to the big dance

articles.description: Darrian Ringo scored 21 on 6-of-10 shooting and Nike Sibande had 13 points and nine rebounds to help Miami (Ohio) beat Ohio 68-55 on Monday night in the first round of the Mid-American Conference Tournament.
articles.headline: Ringo, Miami (Ohio) beat Ohio 68-55 in MAC Tournament

articles.description: Grant Riller scored 25 points for his 13th game this season with 20 or more and top-seed Charleston beat William & Mary 83-73 on Monday night to advance to its second straight Colonial Athletic Association Tournament championship game.
articles.headline: Charleston advances to 2nd straight CAA championship game

videos.description: Auburn's Jared Harper adds to the Tigers' lead over the Tide with an impressive shot from behind the arc.
videos.headline: Harper drills 3-point shot from deep

videos.description: Horace Spencer with a fancy behind the back pass to Malik Dunbar who drains a 3-pointer from the corner.
videos.headline: Tigers' start game off on 8-0 run

videos.description: Horace Spencer gets the ball off the rebound and kicks it out to Malik Dunbar who sink the triple from the top of the wing.
videos.headline: Auburns' Dunbar hits another 3-pointer

videos.description: Collin Sexton drains fade-away jumper seconds before the half-time buzzer. Crimson Tide trail 40-35 at the half.
videos.headline: Alabama's Sexton hits jumper before half-time buzzer

videos.description: Jared Harper knocks down a deep 3-pointer from the top of the arc.
videos.headline: Auburns' Harper drains triple from downtown

videos.description: Dazon Ingram cuts in towards the basket and slams home a two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Crimson Tides' Ingram slams home two-handed dunk

videos.description: Bryce Brown shows off his handle and hits the fade-away jumper.
videos.headline: Tigers' Brown shakes and bakes for a smooth jumper

videos.description: Auburns' Dazon Ingram turns the ball over and Charles Barkley mouths "slow down" after the turnover.
videos.headline: Sir Charles coaching from the stands

videos.description: Malik Dunbar hammers home the first dunk, and Horace Spencer jams in the put-back dunk, and Charles Barkley looks elated in the crowd.
videos.headline: Back-to-back Tigers dunks make Sir Charles happy

videos.description: Head coach Bruce Pearl talks with the SEC Now crew about Auburn's win over Alabama and how playing zone defense affected the Crimson Tide.
videos.headline: Pearl says win over Tide is huge step for Tigers

tracking.trackingName: SEC_NCB Interview (Now Pearl on AUB over Bama) 180221

videos.description: No. 12 Auburn tops their in-state rival Alabama 90-71.
videos.headline: Auburn rolls over Alabama

videos.description: The Tigers force 17 Crimson Tide turnovers and earn 14 steals en route to improving their home record to 14-1.
videos.headline: No. 12 Auburn's defense holds off Bama in 90-71 win
